the GNU GPL-3.0, together with some custom rules.

You can:
- Use the software for free if you do not make money with it
- Change the software
- Share the original or changed version with other people
  (only if they also do not make money with it)
- Run it on a server or offer it online (only non-commercially)

You must:
- Give credit to the author (keep the copyright notice)
- Give the full source code when you share the software
- Give the full source code when you offer the software
  online as a service
- Keep the license text and the copyright notices
- Stop sharing the software on a website if the author asks
  that website to stop

You cannot:
- Use the software to make money
- Sell the software
- Put the software inside a paid product or paid service

The software is given without any warranty.
